[Player 1 Always Starts With 5 Finishers]
author=BigBossman
description=This is mostly handy for matches that don't allow you to select the number of finishers you start with, such as a Royal Rumble Match or Slobber Knocker. It is possible to start with more than 5 finishers by adjusting the value. You'll start with the number of finishers you designate regardless of how many you select to start with. The game won't display more than 5 specials, but will keep track of the number you have.
patch=1,EE,002F1BEA,extended,00000005

[Player 1 Character Modifier]
author=BigBossman
description=These codes will also add players to a match. For example, if you have all 8 character modifiers active & you select a singles match, you will have 8 characters in the ring. In addition, if you have more characters in a singles match, you'll control three of them at the same time. The values that have characters in referee shirts are normally used in special referee matches. When using a character with a referee shirt, you can't build up a special & the referee is gone, but you'll still be able to pin your opponent(s), get counted out, or submit an opponent. To remove characters from a match, simply use the value "FF", but don't use it in a singles match, leaving only one wrestler in the match, or the game will freeze. These codes won't affect Career Mode's cut scenes or storylines, but when the match begins, your designated character(s) will appear. Specials when using the characters with T-Shirts with logos, won't build either.
 
