[Player 1 Role Modifier]
author=BigBossman
description=This will determine the type of participant that each player will be in a match. It is possible to have more than two referees in a single match. If your selected character is designated as interference, the character will appear in the match at a later point. If your selected character is designated as eliminated, you'll be at ringside, but won't be able to enter the ring. The camera won't focus on you either. You will be able to pick up weapons, throw them into the ring, pull the legs of other wrestlers or referees, or attack others on the outside of the ring. If your character is designated as an illegal wrestler, you can enter the ring & attack others.
Values -
00 - Wrestler
01 - Referee
02 - Manager
03 - Interference
04 - Illegal Wrestler
05 - Eliminated, at Ringside
patch=1,EE,00725AEB,extended,00000000

[Player 1 Side Modifier]
author=BigBossman
description=These determine which side a player is on. In order for two or more players to be on the same side or team, they will need to have the same value. If they have a different value, they will be opponents & can pin or submit each other. For Example: Normally you can play a 1-on-3 Handicapped Match, but it won't let you play a 1-on-3 Handicapped Tag match. You would take Player 1's value & set it at "00". Player 2, 3, & 4's value would be set at "01". Then when you start a tag team match, you'll notice that Player 1's partner (Player 3) is siding with the other tag team. Instead of all three of them ganging up on you at once, they have to be tagged in. You can also set the values to create other match type combinations. Be careful when using it in an 8-Man Battle Royal, its a little bit buggy. I played a 1-on-7 Battle Royal. It seemed as if the CPU's movements were all synchronized for the other seven players. This can also affect the referee. If you are playing a 1-on-1 match with no interference, the referee is Player 3. If there are 3 players in a match, the referee is Player 4. If there are 5 wrestlers, the ref is Player 6. ETC. Setting the referee to be an opponent or as someone's teammate may make it to where he doesn't count pinfalls or counts slowly.
patch=1,EE,00725AEC,extended,00000000

[Player 1 Starting Damage Modifier]
author=BigBossman
description=These codes will determine the amount of damage you start a match with.
Values - 
00 - Start With No Damage
80 - Badly Damaged / Can easily be pinned or submitted
